                            <comment id="13667798" author="maysamyabandeh" created="Mon, 27 May 2013 16:25:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The unit test that shows the bug in SparseMatrix.clone()&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13667875" author="tdunning" created="Mon, 27 May 2013 18:38:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like a nice catch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Shouldn&apos;t this test go in MatrixTest instead?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If so, then changing the test matrix to be bigger than 1x1 is helpful:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
  @Test
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void testClone() {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; oldValue = 1.23;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; newValue = 2.34;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt;[][] values = {{oldValue, 3}, {3, 5}, {7, 9}};
    Matrix matrix = matrixFactory(values);
    Matrix clone = matrix.clone();
    clone.set(0, 0, newValue);
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//test whether the update in the clone is reflected in the original matrix
&lt;/span&gt;    assertEquals(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Matrix clone is not independent of the original&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
      oldValue, matrix.get(0, 0), EPSILON);
  }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This uncovers the same problem in PivotMatrix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13667989" author="tdunning" created="Tue, 28 May 2013 00:21:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a revised patch that moves the test up to MatrixTest and then fixes both the bug in SparseVector and the one in PivotedMatrix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13668120" author="maysamyabandeh" created="Tue, 28 May 2013 07:30:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the fix Ted. At some point, perhaps we should also move up TestSparseMatrix.testViewRow() to MatrixTest.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13668131" author="tdunning" created="Tue, 28 May 2013 08:02:34 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;So produce a combined patch!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13668147" author="maysamyabandeh" created="Tue, 28 May 2013 08:25:34 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Ted&apos;s patch + moving up SparseMatrix.testViewRow()&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
